16/07/2009
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Police arrested former Croatian Railways (HZ) Director Davorin Kobak for allegedly embezzling funds from the state-controlled company, local media reported on Wednesday (July 15th).
Two officials from AGIT, a subsidiary of HZ Cargo, were also detained.
The three allegedly embezzled about 3m euros from AGIT via offshore companies.
Anti-corruption office USKOK launched an investigation in February into alleged money laundering practices within the HZ and AGIT.
(Jutarnji List, HRT, HINA, Poslovni Dnevnik - 15/07/09)
